<!-- Begin Intro Row -->
<div class="row intro">
    <div class="label-column">
        Intro
    </div>

    <div class="content-column">
		<b>The largest releases in Document Cloud history. </b> The same year Acrobat celebrated 25 years, I had the opportunity to help drive and ship a massive overhaul to the over 300 million customers.
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Begin Problem Row -->
<div class="row intro">
    <div class="label-column">
        Problem
    </div>
    <div class="content-column">
    Acrobat and PDF together invented a business technology category, but had fallen behind. With the advent of document co-editing, PDF readers embedded in browsers, and open-source PDF solutions the Document Cloud business was under attack.
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Begin Solution Row -->
<div class="row intro">
    <div class="label-column">
        Solution
    </div>
    <div class="content-column">
    Project "Virgo" was a complete visual redesign of the Acrobat ecosystem of products to incorporate Adobe's new design system Spectrum, it added new real-time collaboration cloud service called "DC Review," and made a few billion PDFs accessible with new machine learning capabilities. As a lead on the Adobe Document Cloud design team, I was responsible for Home: the document organization and management experience across desktop and web. 
    </div>
</div>

